column.name: Number
column.comment: A unique number assigned to each order.

column.name: OrderDate
column.comment: The date and time when the order was placed. (MM/DD/YYYY)

column.name: BillTo
column.comment: The sixteen digit credit card number used to place this order. This number should be listed in the credit card table.

column.name: ShipTo
column.comment: The customer number of the person to whom the order is being shipped.

column.name: ShippingMethod
column.comment: The method of shipping for the order.

column.name: TotalPrice
column.comment: The total purchase price of the order.

column.name: Discounts
column.comment: A money value less than or equal to zero representing total discounts.

column.name: ShippingCost
column.comment: The cost of shipping the order.

column.name: Taxes
column.comment: The total tax assessed on the order.

column.name: InvoiceNumber
column.comment: The number of the invoice for the order in which the item was sold.

column.name: ItemNumber
column.comment: A number that uniquely identifies each different product.

column.name: ItemName
column.comment: The name of the product, unique for each item.

column.name: Quantity
column.comment: The number of that item purchased in the particular order.

column.name: PricePerUnit
column.comment: The price per unit of the item.

column.name: ShipFrom
column.comment: The warehouse that this product is being shipping from.

column.name: Number
column.comment: A unique indentifying number assigned to each cutomer.

column.name: CustomerName
column.comment: The name of this customer.

column.name: StreetAddress
column.comment: The street address of the customer.

column.name: City
column.comment: The city in which the customer is located.

column.name: State
column.comment: The state in which the customer is located.

column.name: Zip
column.comment: The zip code of the customer.

column.name: AreaCode
column.comment: The three digit area code of customer's phone number.

column.name: PhoneNumber
column.comment: The customer's phone number (xxx-xxxx);

column.name: Email
column.comment: The customer's email address.

column.name: Number
column.comment: The sixteen digit credit card number, these should be unique.

column.name: NameOnCard
column.comment: The name of the card holder as listed on the card.

column.name: CardType
column.comment: The type of the credit card (VISA, MasterCard, AMEX).

column.name: CustomerNumber
column.comment: The customer number as listed in the Customer table.

column.name: ExpMonth
column.comment: The month (MM) when the card expires.

column.name: ExpYear
column.comment: The year (YY) when the card expires.

column.name: Street
column.comment: The street address registered for the credit card (in case different from customer's address and/or shipping address.

column.name: City
column.comment: The city the billing address is located in.

column.name: State
column.comment: The state the billing address is located in.

column.name: Zip
column.comment: The zip code the billing address is located in.

column.name: AreaCode
column.comment: The area code of the phone number registered with the credit card.

column.name: PhoneNumber
column.comment: The phone number associated with the credit card.

foreignkeyconstraint.comment: Each invoice is billed to a credit card.
Each recipient of a shipped order should be listed in the Customer table.
Each item purchased should have an invoice number of a listed invoice.
Each credit card should be associated with a customer. A customer may have more than one listed credit card.
